article.headline: Liberty 64, East Carolina 56
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Alex McLean scored 17 points, including 13 in the second half, to give Liberty a 64-56 come-from-behind win over East Carolina on Saturday night. McLean's lay-up with 12:16 remaining put the Flames (4-1) ahead 36-35 to stay. The score was part of a 10-point run that put Liberty up by nine with 10:05 left. The Pirates (4-2) got to within four several times late in the game. A layup by Darrell Jenkins cut Liberty's lead to 60-56 with 1:31 remaining, but it was the last time East Carolina would score. Larry Blair scored 15 points and B.J. Jenkins had 12 for Liberty. East Carolina rocketed out to a 17-3 lead in the first eight minutes, led by Courtney Captain's seven points during the run. The Pirates held a 26-21 lead at the half. But in the second, Liberty shot 61.5 percent from the field and made 10 of 14 free throws to spur their comeback. Captain had 16 points and Jenkins scored 13 for East Carolina.
